value.0: I welcome you into the ShadowGuard, my <brother/sister>...
Would you like some help in your mission?
As you wish.
Very good, <mister/missus> <LastName>.
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 9. USING THIS FOR TESTING AT THE MOMENT! >>
I'm glad to have you with us, <FirstName>...
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_2_MAIN" >>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 2. >>
Talk to Vhorkas...
No time for words now, friend... Time to go!
Even demons bleed...
RARGHH!
Destroy him, Harkon! Tear that fool apart!
Are you ready to go again? We should make our way to the docks at once.
All right, I'll wait here in the shadows. Please return when you're ready to move on.
Talk to Markius. He needs a word with you.
<StartAction>[The ranger, Lyen Silverblade, is almost invisible against the pitch of night. Only the piercing whites of his eyes are clearly visible as he stares right through you.]</Start>
Ah, I was hoping you'd arrived unscathed. You've done much for my friend, Tarin. Please allow me to escort you to the ship. I can cut you a safe path with great ease in this darkness.
There you are coward! You abandoned Tarin to the Nightcrawlers. Be gone, you pathetic wretch, before my blade finds your throat.
I recognize you. You were there when the Nightcrawlers took my small friend, Tarin.
I haven't had any luck in locating him. Hopefully I'll have more luck once we clear the Crimson Prophet's rabble from the streets. Knowing Tarin, he'll find his way free.
Do you need any assistance? I'm sure that in this darkness I could cut a path to the ship for you.
I recognize you. You were are the Ravenclaw tavern earlier.
Yes, I've cut through many hordes while under Markius' command and in this darkness I could cut you a path to the ship, if you like.
Greetings, I am Lyen Silverblade.
Okay... Come back if you need me help...
It is good to meet you too, <FirstName>.Would you like my assistance? I could easily get you to the ship unnoticed in this darkness.
<StartAction>[Lyen removes his blade form its sheath.]</Start> Then it's time we were off, <FirstName>!
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_TARI" >>
Speak with Markius... He needs to talk with you.
<StartAction>[Lyen Silverblade, the dark Ranger of the ShadowGuard, grunts as you approach.]</Start>
What do you need, <FirstName>?
<StartAction>[Brukus just grunts in farewell, and returns to his business.]</Start>
<StartAction>[An unusual expression of fear comes over the Half-Orc's greenish-grey face.]</Start> That be bad trial... Me not like to thinks about it...
Lots of weird things in trial... Make me head hurt bad, see things... Me just bash... and bash... and bash... til me found way out... Me not ever want to do again...
<StartAction>[The Half-Orc seems to lose himself in the memory of his Final Initiation, and any further questions you ask do not seem to help further the subject...]</Start>
What you want know?
Overlord not like me, think me dangerous... Markius have to tell him how strong me is all the time. Me not have much to do wit' Overlord...
But him wise man, speak to Emperor lots. He helps us find Prophet, then we bash bad men good! Markius be happy then!
Little Tarin not big, but him got big brain. Him and me make good team... He does quick talkin', me does quick bashin'!
Him good at cards, too. Best me ever seen. Me not really know how to play cards good, though...
She strong witch. Death not 'nough to get away from Kara. She bring you back from other world if she need you, so strong is her...

She nice to me, though. Not nice as Markius, but Kara not treat me like animal either. And she got pretty eyes... <StartAction>[Brukus abruptly falls silent, his greenish-grey cheeks blushing red...]</Start>
Markius is a great man. He brought me into the ShadowGuard... He treated me like a man, not a thief...
I'll do anything he asks... I'd take the blade for him if I must!
<StartAction>[Lyen snarls at you angrily.]</Start> After your betrayal of my friend? Just watch your back, <FirstName>, or there'll be a dagger in it soon enough.
<StartAction>[Lyen just snarls again, and you believe it would be wise to leave before he grows any angrier...]</Start>
I'd rather not talk about that right now...
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> No! Go waste someone else's time.
<StartAction>[Success]</Start> Alright, let's see...
<StartAction>[Lyen smiles]</Start> Its the very least I can do, after what you've done for Tarin. Ask anything.
I was a cutthroat since the day I was born. I lived in the outlands with a gypsy group of thieves and assassins.
I never liked the life I had, but it was the only life I knew. It was vicious. Men and women clawing at each other over food and gold.
One night I left the band and made my way to the city. The nights were cold and the road was hard, but eventually I found a civilized place.
It was Laceri, a city of the Empire. As I made my way though the gates I met Markius. I thought for sure he would cast me out, but instead he directed me to an Inn and a warm meal.
That night there was an attack on the city; the gypsy band I had escaped had followed me to town. They cut through the doors in the dead of night and started pillaging the town.

I couldn't let them destroy this bastion of hope I had discovered. So I fought them. When the sun rose the next morning Markius and I were standing over a hundred fallen gypsies. And I... I was a ShadowGuard.
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_ST_1_MAIN" >>
<< Activates "N_TALK_SWITCH" if "N_MODULE_STAGE" is 1. >>
Thank you for saving my friend, <FirstName>... You're a good <man/woman>, one day I'll repay you this debt!
<StartAction>[Lyen's whole body coils in rage.]</Start> You let them take Tarin?! I'll cut his name into your worthless hide! You coward!
<StartAction>[Lyen waves a dagger at you but seems to calm a bit.]</Start> You'd better hope so! If Tarin comes to harm, I'll be back, <FirstName>, but you won't see me coming.
<StartAction>[Without another word, the dark figure dashes from the chamber, leaving you alone with your earnings from Malthar...]</Start>
I must find Tarin! Please, <FirstName>, will you help me?
<StartAction>[Lyen still seems groggy from the effects of Malthar's tainted ale, but he slowly rises to look at you.]</Start> What! They took Tarin! We must find him, <FirstName>!
<StartAction>[Lyen roars with anger.]</Start> Then step aside, coward! I will carve my way through those fools until I return Tarin to safety.
<StartAction>[Lyen's eyes flare in anger.]</Start> Reward!? How about you help my friend or I remove your digits with a rusted blade. Does that pique your interest any?
Good answer, <FirstName>. I'll cut their throats for this insult. No one crosses a Silverblade and survives long enough to brag about it.
<StartAction>[Lyen snarls.]</Start> No, I need to go with you! Tarin is my ally. I will not sit idly by while he's in danger.
<StartAction>[Lyen does not seemed pleased with your answer, but slowy nods in agreement.]</Start> I will trust in your prowess,  <FirstName>. Do not disappoint me.
<StartAction>[Lyen's grey eyes pierce you like daggers]</Start> If I learn that you let Tarin suffer, I will hunt you to the ends of the earth.
Let's track down this Malthar fellow and retreive Tarin. Once he's safe I'll carve some respect into the ranks of those "Nightcrawlers."
Why does Tarin insist on gambling? We usually lose more then we gain.
Who is that?
<StartAction>[The man's cold gaze fixes upon you.]</Start> If you need something, talk to the halfling.
<StartAction>[The man's cold gaze fixes upon you.]</Start> If you need something, talk to the halfling.

Comment.value: Default dialogue when the henchman is a member of the player's party.

value.0: What do you wish of me, <FirstName>?
<StartAction>[Lyen eyes you for a moment, and turns away.]</Start>
Are you certain? I feel I may still be of some use to you.
I'm glad to hear you say that. We should start moving, there is still much to do.
Very well, I'll return to the Ravenclaw tavern. You can find me there if you are ever in need of my skills.
As you wish, <FirstName>.
My services are at your command, <FirstName>.
Very well.
Very well.
Fine, I shall leave such things to you.
Of course, I can always help with that.
And walk out in the open? All right, if you wish.
My pleasure.
Very well, I will no longer search while we are moving.
Very well, I will no longer search while we are moving.
I will try to heal you even if I am being attacked at close range.
Very well, I will heal you only if I am not in hand-to-hand combat.
As you wish.
And how far away do you need me?
I do hope you are not trying tell me something, but I shall do as you wish.
Not too close, then, and not too far. I get it.
Fine. I shall stay as close as is reasonable.
I can do that. When the combat begins I'll rush in and use melee weapons.
Of course. When the combat begins I'll stay back and attack with my ranged weapons from a distance. I'll switch weapons if the enemies get too close.
What would you like me to do?
Very well. I will avoid melee combat unless I am cornered.
As you wish, <FirstName>.
That may be hard to judge, but I shall do my best.
Very well, I'll wait until the last possible moment.
Very well. I will do what I feel is best.
There is no need to scout ahead. We are safe here.
I'll see what I can find.
Hold on, then. Give me a moment to rest, and I'll be ready to assist you.
<< Set owner's journal quest to "JT_PREL_TARI" >>
No, I work better alone.
Yes, I would.
Not just yet. You wait here.
Let's go, Lyen.
Where is Tarin now?
You're with the ShadowGuard? I had no idea...
I really must be on my way...
Nice to meet you, Lyen. I'm <FullName>.
Actually, I'm thinking of choosing someone else...
Sounds just like what I need. Let's go.
I don't need anything right now. Farewell, Brukus...
Can you tell me a bit about the Final Initiation?
Can I ask you about the other ShadowGuard?
Actually, let me ask you about something else...
Can you tell me a bit about Overlord Vhorkas?
I'd like to know more about Tarin Lightfingers...
What are your thoughts on Kara Dy'nesh?
Tell me what you can of Markius Albright...
I see. Let me ask you about another ShadowGuard member...
Lyen, can you tell me a bit about yourself?
All right, all right! Sorry to have bothered you...
<StartAction>[Persuade]</Start> Come, Lyen. We are friends, and I would like to hear your tale...
So what's your tale, Lyen?
Well, let me ask you about something else, Lyen...
Come, Lyen, have you no faith in your little friend?
Don't worry, Tarin was able to escape all the same.
I'll help you, Lyen.
Tarin brought this on himself. Why should I get involved?
<StartAction>[Allow Lyen to leave.]</Start>
Wait, maybe I should help... Let's go together?
I might be willing to help, if there was a reward...
No reward, no aid from me. That's how I operate!
<StartAction>[Gulp.]</Start> Good enough for me... Let's go!
I agree, Lyen. I don't want anything to befall him.
That's really not necessary, Lyen...
I can do better on my own, Lyen. Stay here.
<StartAction>[Sigh]</Start> Then please, join me Lyen.
Let's go then.
I think we should part paths for the moment.
Not at the moment, Lyen. Perhaps later.
I would like to manage your inventory.

value.0: Back to my other questions
Could you please not disable traps?
Could you please disable traps?
Heal me even if there are enemies near you.
Do not heal me if there are enemies near you.
Let's talk about your weapon-switching tactics.
I don't want you to engage in close-range combat at all. Move away from the enemy if they are too close!
Be aggressive. If you see enemies getting any closer than 6 meters or so, charge with melee!
I think you should switch to melee if the enemy is at a medium distance, between 4 and 5 meters away.
Since you're so good with your missile weapon, wait until the enemy gets relatively close, say less than 3 meters, before you switch to a melee weapon.
I want you to trust your instinct as to when to switch betwen melee and missile weapons.
Scout ahead for enemies. Engage in combat if they are nearby; otherwise return to me.
